==English==

===Noun===
'''bridge'''

#A [[construction]] or [[natural]] [[feature]] that [[span]]s a [[divide]].
#{{cattag|card games}}: A [[card game]] played normally with four players playing as two teams of two players each.
#The [[upper]] [[bony]] [[ridge]] of the [[human]] [[nose]]
#A [[replacement]] for one or [[several]] [[teeth]]
#{{nautical}} an [[elevated]] [[platform]] above the [[upper]] [[deck]] of a [[mechanically]] [[propelled]] [[ship]] from which it is [[navigated]] and from where all [[activities]] on [[deck]] can be [[seen]] and [[controlled]] by the [[captain]] etc (Note: smaller ships have a [[wheelhouse]], and [[sailing]] ships were controlled from the [[quarterdeck]])

